  "response_text": "A hand slides a pale, scalloped glass plate onto a dark tabletop near a softly lit window. The plate is filled with small, foil-wrapped chocolates in Valentine colours: bright pink, red, and white. The hand, with dark nail polish, gently adjusts the candies and then lifts one pink-wrapped piece from the edge of the plate.\n\nWarm daylight streams across the face of a young adult woman with long, dark brown hair. Her face is partly hidden at first by a hazy veil of steam or bright window glare, then becomes clearer as she looks downward with a small, pleased smile. She appears relaxed and thoughtful, in a softly lit café-like setting.\n\nAt a patterned café table, the woman opens a glossy burgundy clutch purse. Beside it sits a cup of coffee topped with pale foam. She reaches into the purse and pulls out small pink foil-wrapped Dove chocolates. She places several of them onto a small tray already holding coins, positioning the chocolates among the change as though leaving an extra treat along with payment or a tip. The rich pink wrappers stand out against the metal coins and the decorative tabletop.\n\nThe setting widens to reveal a café counter. A young adult barista with short curly hair, wearing a light shirt over a darker long-sleeved top, works at an espresso machine. A chalkboard menu behind the counter lists drinks such as café latte, mocha, Americano, and tea. The dark-haired woman is visible in the background, seated or standing nearby, while the barista appears focused on preparing coffee.\n\nOutside on a residential street, a pink mailbox stands in the foreground with a simple hand-drawn heart on its side. In the background, the same dark-haired woman approaches along the sidewalk, wearing a brown coat and carrying something small in one hand. The mailbox door is open, revealing a red interior. Inside, she places a Valentine-style card or small envelope decorated with a pale ribbon design and a shiny red heart-shaped candy or sticker attached near the bottom. Her gloved or coat-sleeved hand slides the item neatly into the mailbox, leaving it visible inside.\n\nBack indoors by bright curtains, the woman holds up a silver Dove chocolate wrapper close to her face. The wrapper has a white heart shape printed on it with the words “Be my valentine.” and the Dove logo beneath. She looks toward it and then toward the viewer with a playful, satisfied smile, presenting the wrapper like a small Valentine message.\n\nShe then reclines in a cream-coloured chair near sheer curtains glowing with sunlight. She wears a pink top and light grey pants, with a bracelet or watch on her wrist. A red Valentine card or envelope rests in her lap, along with pink Dove chocolate wrapping. She brings a piece of chocolate toward her mouth, settling comfortably into the chair as she enjoys it.\n\nThe imagery shifts to a close view of glossy melted chocolate swirling in smooth, circular ripples. The chocolate surface is dark brown with lighter highlights, moving like a thick, silky whirlpool.\n\nFinally, Dove chocolate packages appear arranged on a flowing bed of melted chocolate. Three pink and red packages stand upright, each prominently showing the black Dove logo. The front pink package includes decorative heart graphics and images of individually wrapped chocolates. The red package at the back suggests a dark chocolate variety, while another pink package sits to the right. At the bottom of the image, small white text reads “facebook.com/dovechocolate.”",
